{"add":{"doc":{"id":"c5cd0ea2600e034cc94062601c5f7c6dc715d8328ff13649d8ea3c3a05ecb016","url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/24/LiveToTellNewYork.jpg/170px-LiveToTellNewYork.jpg","previous":[],"after":["In the United States, True Blue debuted at number 28 on the Billboard 200 and reached number one on the issue dated August 16, 1986.[88] It stayed on the top position for five consecutive weeks and on the chart for a total of 82 weeks. The album also reached a peak of number 47 on the Top R&B/Hip-Hop Albums chart.[89] True Blue was certified seven times platinum by the Recording Industry Association of America (RIAA) for shipment of over seven million units, making it Madonna's third best-selling album in the United States, behind Like a Virgin (1984) and The Immaculate Collection (1990).[90] After the advent of the Nielsen SoundScan era in 1991, the album sold a further 404,000 copies.[91] In Canada, the album debuted at number 73 on the RPM albums chart for the issue of July 5, 1986.[92] The album climbed rapidly upwards and reached number one on the issue dated August 9, 1986.[93] It stayed at the top for nine weeks and was present on the chart for 77 weeks.[94][95] True Blue was certified diamond by the Canadian Recording Industry Association (CRIA) for shipment of one million copies.[96]"]}}}